  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale-input variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The primary experimental dataset carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-14, predating the modelRevisionDate of 2025-11-03. The assessment narrative characterises the November revision as a turbulence-coefficient refinement that is 'not material' to the dataset's applicability; however, no formal re-validation against the revised model build was performed, constituting a W-EP-03 stale-input-data condition.",
