      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version controlled; release notes and regression test suite documented for ANSYS Fluent 2023 R2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R2 is a commercially validated solver with documented QA procedures. Version control records confirm consistent solver version across all simulation runs. Regression test suite results archived in project repository."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark cases for rotating-frame turbulent flow at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent benchmark results for Taylor-Couette flow and rotating channel flow are available in vendor documentation and independently reproduced by the project team. Code verification is deemed adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for velocity magnitude and wall shear stress at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 4.2 M, medium 9.8 M, fine 22.1 M cells). GCI for velocity magnitude ranged from 1.8% to 3.9%; GCI for wall shear stress ranged from 2.1% to 4.7%. All values below 5% threshold. Medium mesh selected for production runs as the cost-accuracy optimum."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental flow conditions (viscosity, density, rotational speed, flow rates) documented and match CFD boundary conditions within stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, 36% w/w) properties measured at 37 °C and confirmed within ±1.5% of CFD input values. Pump rotational speed verified via optical tachometer. Flow rates set by calibrated Coriolis meter (±0.5% FS). All experimental conditions logged and traceable to dataset morrison-piv-hemolysis-exp-2025q4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index within 15% of experimental mean across all five operating points; velocity field mean absolute error < 10%.",
      "rationale": "CFD RH index predictions ranged from 0.81 to 1.19 relative to experimental means (worst-case 12% deviation). Velocity field MAE across all PIV planes was 7.3%. Both metrics satisfy acceptance criteria. Comparison performed against model build v2r2; the subsequent v2r3 revision adjusted the SST k-omega turbulence model C-mu coefficient by 2.4% to improve impeller-passage predictions — the assessment team judged this change not material to the hemolysis dataset's relevance, but no formal re-validation run was executed against v2r3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (RH index, wall shear stress, velocity magnitude) are directly linked to the hemolysis prediction objective and accepted by the COU.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the primary regulatory QoI for CPB device assessment. Velocity magnitude and wall shear stress are mechanistically linked to red blood cell damage and are standard surrogate QoIs in the literature. All three QoIs are explicitly referenced in the COU intendedUse statement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same pump geometry and operating envelope as the COU; blood analogue fluid properties within physiological range.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at the five COU flow-speed operating points. Blood analogue viscosity and density match physiological blood properties within accepted tolerances (ASTM F1841). The validation scenario is judged representative of the COU envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; commercial solver documentation accepted as sufficient.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, explicit numerical solver error quantification beyond code verification is not required. Reliance on ANSYS Fluent's documented iterative convergence criteria (residuals < 1e-5) and mass-balance checks (< 0.01%) is acceptable."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; simulation setup reviewed by independent engineer.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup (boundary conditions, turbulence model selection, rotating reference frame configuration) performed by a senior CFD engineer not involved in the original setup. No setup errors identified. Formal use-error quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; turbulence model selection justified by literature precedent.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published precedent for rotating blood-contacting devices (Hariharan et al. 2011; Thamsen et al. 2015). Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2 but is noted as a future improvement opportunity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) documented with sources and uncertainty estimates; inputs traceable to measured or published values.",
      "rationale": "Geometry imported from manufacturer CAD (rev B drawing, tolerance ±0.05 mm). Fluid properties sourced from laboratory measurements archived in dataset morrison-boundary-conditions-nominal (dataVintage 2025-10-14). Boundary conditions derived from the same dataset. The model was subsequently revised on 2025-11-03 to refine turbulence closure; the input dataset was not re-collected post-revision because the team assessed the geometric and fluid-property inputs as unaffected by the turbulence coefficient change. This assessment was made informally without documented re-validation, representing a potential gap in traceability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; single pump unit used for all validation experiments.",
      "rationale": "A single representative pump unit was used for all PIV and hemolysis validation experiments. Sample-to-sample variability assessment is not required at MRL 2. Manufacturing tolerances for the test unit are documented in the test report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD boundary condition values match experimental test conditions within combined measurement uncertainty for all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Boundary condition equivalency confirmed by direct comparison of logged experimental conditions against CFD inputs for all five operating points. Maximum discrepancy in flow rate: 0.3% (within Coriolis meter uncertainty). Maximum discrepancy in rotational speed: 0.2% (within tachometer uncertainty). Fluid property equivalency confirmed by laboratory measurement certificates archived in dataset morrison-boundary-conditions-nominal."
    }
